Governor Nyesom Wike of Rivers State, the governor of Sokoto State, Aminu Tambuwal, Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi of Enugu State, Nasarawa State Governor, Abdullahi Sule and the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila are currently in Benue State for the commissioning ceremony of newly constructed Ultra-morden Tor Tiv Palace in Gboko Local Government of the state. Also to be commissioned is another three major roads in Gboko newly constructed by the Governor Samuel Ortom’s administration. The event is scheduled to take place by 10am Thursday morning.  DAILY POST gathered that some of the invitees such as the Rivers State Governor would be awarded chieftaincy title during the event. DAILY POST recalls that the State Governor, who visited the Palace to inspect the projects recently, scheduled the commissioning for April 8 (today). The Tor Tiv, Professor James Ayatse, had commended the Governor for constructing such an “edifice as palace, which is one of the best for any traditional ruler in the country”, stressing that he would continue to enjoy their royal blessings. 